games.comment: Kelvin Benjamin had an excellent debut, hauling in 6 of his 8 targets for 92 yards and a touchdown. The Buccaneers had no answer for him. Benjamin looks like he's going to be a stud. Meanwhile, Greg Olsen paced the team with 11 targets, snagging 8 of them for 83 yards and a score.    The Panthers ran the ball extremely well, registering 72 yards on 14 carries.
